<recipe>
<title>
Pickled Red Onions
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1 large red onion
6 tablespoons apple cider vinegar
1 tablespoon agave nectar
1/4 teaspoon salt
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Thinly slice red onion, and place in colander.
In a dish large enough to hold onion, mix together vinegar, agave, and salt. Set aside.
Boil a pot of water.
Pour over onion slices, and shake to drain.
Add onion slices to vinegar mixture.
Cover, and chill overnight before serving.
</instructions>
</recipe>
